  • Did you know: the "Golden Age" of English biography emerged in the late 1700s. The classic works of the period were Samuel Johnson's Critical Lives of the Poets (1779-81) and James Boswell's massive Life of Johnson (1791).
    • #Newline
  • Did you know: the Jewish holy scripture is an anthology of some of the earliest biographies in existence#Comma detailing the lives of chiefs#Comma kings#Comma tribes#Comma patriarchs and prophets.
    • #Newline
  • Did you know: probably the most famous German autobiography is still Goethe's Dichtung und Wahrheit.
    • #Newline
  • Did you know: the first known biographies were written by scribes commissioned by the various rulers of antiquity: ancient Assyria#Comma ancient Babylonia#Comma ancient Egypt#Comma ancient Mesopotamia#Comma among others.
    • #Newline
  • Did you know: Sir Thomas Malory wrote the most famous fictional biography of the Middle Ages with Le Morte d'Arthur about the life of King Arthur.
    • #Newline
  • Did you know: the 2006 Pulitzer Prize for Biography or Autobiography went to American Prometheus: The Triumph and Tragedy of J. Robert Oppenheimer by Kai Bird and Martin J. Sherwin
